						<summary>

						<p>On the Garuḍa-pillar set up in front of the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>[KŌMAṬI]VĒMA.</p>						

						<p>1418 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1340, Viḷambi, Kārttīka Śu. 11, [Saturday]. We come across Adhika and Nijakārttīka months in this year and the equivalent dates are November 9, Wednesday, or October 10, Monday of 1418 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of land, house and garden by 22 soldiers <hi rend="italic">(ekkuaṭīlu)</hi> of Velanṭūru on behalf <hi rend="italic">(peṁpuna �rightarrow� paṁpuna)</hi> of the Vēmamaṇḍalēśvara to the temple Agastyēśvarasvāmi. It also records some gift to the temple of Mailāradēva.</p>						

						</summary>
